						& my talents</h2>
					</header>
					<p>Born and raised in Seattle. I have a BS degree in <strong>Computer Science</strong> from Gonzaga University and a certification in <strong>User Experience Design</strong> from General Assembly.</p>
					<p>Out of school I spent three years as a <strong>software engineer</strong> in a corporate structure. Wanting more control over the design of products I left to become a freelance <strong>UX designer</strong>. Now I design and create a variety of products, from webpages and apps to logos and photographs. Being a freelance designer has allowed me the freedom to work on a diverse set of projects to gain unique experience.</p>
					<p>During my time as a freelancer I have worked with many local and California based clients. I helped <strong>start a company</strong> and create an app called <a href="projects/dealtapp">DealTapp</a>. I am currently their lead UX Designer.</p>
					<p></p>
					<p>My strengths are in user research & analytics, information architecture, and interaction design.</p>
					<p>My tools of choice are: Sketch, Illustrator, Photoshop, Invision, HTML, CSS, JavaScript, Ruby on Rails, GIT, and Google Analytics.</p>
